Concept:
Main configuration emacs file (init.el) is constructed in
following way:

1) Collect set of enabled vendor packages
2) Generate paths based on 1)
3) Load personal settings for each package in /personalization
   folder
4) ...
5) Profit!

Mini how-to:

ruby init.rb - to install all submodules
ruby generate-config.rb - to build init.el
cd ~/.emacs.d/vendor/rinari
git submodule init
git submodule update

Panel:
All modules which are presumed to be loaded have
apropriate lines in panel.yml
One can easy turn on or turn off some module by
changing 1 to 0 in that file

Requirements:
rcodetools gem (if rcodetools enabled in panel.yml)
ruby-debuf (if rdebug enabled)

